      "text": [
        " : سُئِلَ عَنِ اَلرَّجُلِ يُعْتِقُ جَارِيَتَهُ عَنْ دُبُرٍ أَ يَطَؤُهَا إِنْ شَاءَ أَوْ يُنْكِحُهَا أَوْ يَبِيعُ خِدْمَتَهَا حَيَاتَهُ قَالَ \"نَعَمْ أَيَّ ذَلِكَ شَاءَ فَعَلَ\"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.3462 - Aban narrated from Abu Maryam, from Abu Abdullah (as), who was asked about a man who made his bondwoman mudabbar (to be freed after his death).\nImam (as) was asked: \"Can he have relations with her if he wishes, or marry her off, or sell her service during his lifetime?\"\nImam (as) said: \"Yes, he may do any of these if he wishes.\""
        ]
      }
    },
